   <refnamediv>
       <refname>shiftr</refname>
               <refpurpose>mimics gauss function shiftr </refpurpose>
   </refnamediv>
 
        <refsynopsisdiv>
               <title>CALLING SEQUENCE</title>
               <synopsis>[matout]=shiftr(matin,shifts,val)</synopsis>
        </refsynopsisdiv>
 
        <refsection>
           <title>PARAMETERS</title>
           <variablelist>
           <varlistentry>
 
           <term>Input</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> matin </term> =    input (mxn) matrix</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term> shifts </term> =    (mx1) vectors of shifting values</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term> val </term> =    value to fill the holes</para></listitem>
 
 
 
<listitem><para>&#160;</para></listitem>
 
           </varlistentry>
 
          <varlistentry>
 
          <term>Output</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> matout </term> =    (mxn) transformed matrix</para></listitem>
 
 
          </varlistentry>
          </variablelist>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
Function that mimics gauss function shiftr: shifts rows of a matrix according to a vector of shifts and fills the holes with a prespecified value. 

        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>EXAMPLE</title>
              <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
A = matrix([1:15],3,5);B=shiftr(A,[2 3 -2],0)// returns:
// B  =//!   0.    0.     1.     4.    7. !//!   0.    0.     0.     2.    5. !//!   9.    12.    15.    0.    0. !
               ]]></programlisting>
        </refsection>
 
